# prose_translation = Having arisen then from an improvisational start — both it and comedy, the former from the leaders of the dithyramb, the latter from the leaders of the phallic songs which even now remain in use in many of our cities — it grew little by little as they developed whatever was manifest in it; and tragedy, after undergoing many changes, stopped when it attained its own nature.
# literal_translation = Having-come but therefore from beginning improvisational — and itself and the comedy, and the indeed from the leaders the dithyramb, the but from the the phallic which still and now in many of-the cities remain being-used — according to small it-increased advancing-further as-much was-becoming manifest of-it; and many changes having-changed the tragedy stopped, since it-held the own nature.
